> i reject the premise that we should be supporting systems with very low memory through the default configuration

@darosior I think we first need to establish what the minimum supported memory is that we support with default configuration. "Very low" can mean different things to different people. Currently we can support running indefinitely on 2GB VMs with default configuration. This is a popular cheap format (https://aws.amazon.com/ec2/instance-types/t2/) for running (not syncing) bitcoind. I don't think that counts as "very low" memory (but others may disagree). The docs in reduce-memory.md can configure running a node in < 500MB of RAM, which I would call "very low".

Bumping to 1GB of RAM without checking available memory will definitely break this 2GB usecase with default configuration, since we don't clear the dbcache periodically anymore.

